com.bluegosling.collections

Interface ImmutableMap<K,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - the type of keys in the map
    V - the type of values in the map
    All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<ImmutableMap.Entry<K,V>>, SizedIterable<ImmutableMap.Entry<K,V>>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ImmutableSortedMap<K,V>, PersistentMap<K,V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractImmutableMap, HamtPersistentMap

    public interface ImmutableMap<K,V>
extends SizedIterable<ImmutableMap.Entry<K,V>>
    An immutable, read-only set of key+value mappings. This interface is similar to the standard Map interface except that it defines no mutation operations.

    The remove() operation of an immutable map's iterator() always throws UnsupportedOperationException. Similarly the iterator() for any of the collection views of the map will also always throw UnsupportedOperationException.
